Missing Anti-clickjacking Header
MEDIUM
ğŸ“ URL: http://localhost/DVWA/login.php
ğŸ”§ Parameter: x-frame-options
ğŸ“‹ Description: The response does not protect against 'ClickJacking' attacks. It should include either Content-Security-Policy with 'frame-ancestors' directive or X-Frame-Options.
ğŸ¯ CWE ID: 1021
ğŸ”— Reference: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/X-Frame-Options

ğŸ’¼ Business Impact

Users tricked into performing unintended actions through hidden interface elements.

ğŸ’° Financial Impact: Unauthorized transactions + user account compromise

ğŸ¯ Attack Scenario

Website embedded invisibly in malicious page, users think they're clicking harmless buttons but actually perform sensitive operations.
